Text.Value: It's about time Halsin actually stepped up and joined us properly - he's certainly been taking up space at camp for long enough.
I can't imagine you're too pleased to have the likes of Balthazar prowling around in there.
Lae'zel has a dangerous look in her eyes - let's just hope she reserves those impulses for any common foes.
Mystra has forsaken Gale entirely. A crushing blow... but he is strong enough to persevere, I think.
Mystra has forsaken Gale entirely. Imagine how he must be feeling... I doubt I could go on, if Lady Shar turned on me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Concerned. 'A crushing blow' = SH turned from Shar. 'I doubt I could go on' = SH loyal to Shar
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 181 - COM Gale met Mystra - failed to earn forgiveness

Text.Value: This place... there's a power in these shadows, I can sense it. It's ancient, familiar...
I'm glad you saw his ploy for what it really was.
You have the audacity to flaunt how you stole from my people? Perhaps I should surrender you and this artefact.
We're still in this fight. Time we got higher.
Nevertheless, as quirks go, that's a new one for me.
Bravo - you had me worried for a moment.
I... I defied Lady Shar. She won't stand for this... we can talk later - I need to get out of here first.

EditorData.NodeContext: Worried/can't believe what she just did (spared Nightsong). This occurs right afterwards while still in the Shadowfell, before the consequences of defying Shar have kicked in.

Text.Value: I assume you are joking.
My orders were to keep the artefact safe, not pry into it... but I'd be lying if I said I wasn't curious as to what exactly it's hiding...
I thought I was the one most burdened with secrets - seems I was very mistaken. All this time we've been fighting and fleeing from the Absolute, and we've one of their figureheads in our midst.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quietly taken aback/unpacking what she's learned (dark urge player had in the past been a leader of the Absolute cult, but no longer remembers)

Text.Value: There must be more to the artefact. You were sent to take it - you must know why it's so important.
Better than hating the place without remembering why.
The Gauntlet of Shar... I can't believe it. I can't believe we found the Dark Lady's sacred crucible.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little overawed (may not actually be in the place she's referring to at the time)

Text.Value: I didn't realise you were so... well-versed in mental and emotional torment.
This place is quite something. I just hope it doesn't spring a leak.
So it's the Blade of Avernus now, Wyll? I suppose that's a new sort of frontier.
So Wyll's the Blade of Avernus now? I suppose that's a new sort of frontier for him.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 135 - Wyll Blade of Avernus Decision

Text.Value: This place is like a glimpse into the future - no need to raise an army when you can just build one.
I'll wager they'll thank you with a blade through the heart. You're tainted in their eyes, same as me. And your best chance is to stay close to the artefact.
Minthara is in Orin's clutches. Either we try to mount a rescue, or pay for her release with Gortash's life.
The Shadowfell... this is Lady Shar's power in its purest form. Nothing can resist her will here.
So that's how you win Mystra's forgiveness - self-sacrifice? I'm sorry, Gale. That can't be what you wanted to hear.
What do you think?
This is it... where I was raised, trained... hells, it's strange to be back.
Our new friend with the myriad limbs seems to know this route well. I just hope we can keep the ruse up once we reach our destination...
It doesn't seem so long ago that Minthara would have sought to kill us, and now we've welcomed her along. We're nothing if not magnanimous.
... but he also stared as if we were the banquet, rather than the one on the table.
I don't want to talk about it.
Damn. I was hoping my imagination had gotten the better of me, but this must be something more.
It seems Gale has made amends with Mystra. Good for him - though I don't see any such reconciliation between myself and Shar any time soon...
It seems Gale has made amends with Mystra. Good for him - though his choice of goddesses leaves something to be desired...

EditorData.NodeContext: Supportive. 'Reconciliation' = SH turned from Shar. ''choice of goddesses' = SH is loyal to Shar
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 180 - COM Gale met Mystra - forgiven

Text.Value: It's an effective trick. Watch out for it. And for Raphael.
Overwhelming. Worship of Lady Shar is usually discreet by nature. Her holy sites have to be modest, well-hidden. But that place... I never knew such grandeur had been built in her honour.

EditorData.NodeContext: Awestruck by a Shar temple she entered (may not necessarily be in the place she's referring to at present) Arc: Shadowheart remains loyal to Shar.

Text.Value: No matter. We've dealt with every other oddity thrown at us lately - we can handle this one too.

EditorData.NodeContext: Working past her surprise. Time to buckle down and deal with the situation (overture from a devil)

Text.Value: Moonrise Towers... if this is indeed the very centre of the Absolute's schemes, then the source of our problem must be in here somewhere.
I didn't think I'd live to see the day when you turned your back on your queen, but all things considered... good for you.
I didn't think I'd live to see the day when Lae'zel turned her back on Vlaakith, but all things considered... good for her.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 141 - Vlaakith camp/Lae'zel Orpheus path after

Text.Value: 'The Blade of Frontiers'. Let's hope Wyll lives up to his name - we'll need all the help we can get.
I... I don't know. Lady Shar expects me to act without question... but I need to think. I need to be sure this is what I want.

EditorData.NodeContext: Conflicted. Enough doubts have been sown throughout the narrative that SH is unsure if she can do what Shar wants (sacrifice Nightsong)

Text.Value: Your gullibility would be endearing, if it didn't lead us into danger.
So, no deal with Raphael. I wouldn't want to give him the satisfaction, anyway.
I'm sorry, Gale. You tried. Mystra was wrong to turn on you, no matter what mistakes you made in the past.
Mystra was never worthy of your devotion, Gale. She will rue the day she turned on you, I am sure.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sympathetic. 'I'm sorry, Gale. You tried' = SH turrned from Shar. 'She will rue the day' = SH loyal to Shar
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 178 - Avatar Gale met Mystra - failed to earn forgiveness

Text.Value: Unless I'm wrong, of course.
No doubts at all? He seemed powerful and very knowledgeable about our problem...
Jaheira's adept at keeping secrets - and for good reason. She was wise to try and keep her family safe... I just wish I could've done the same.
Jaheira's adept at keeping secrets - to conceal a family is no mean feat. Perhaps her skills lean more towards the Dark Lady than she realises...
Use your shared connection. See what she's really thinking.
I... I failed. I failed Lady Shar. She won't stand for this... we can talk later - I need to get out of here first.

EditorData.NodeContext: Worried/can't believe what she just did failed to sacrifice Nightsong). This occurs right afterwards while still in the Shadowfell, before the consequences of defying Shar have kicked in.

Text.Value: We may need to increase our camp provisions now that we have Karlach along for the journey - those muscles don't run on fresh air, I'll wager. Still, she'll be useful in a fight.
...agh! I can feel you - get out of my head!
Actually, I've changed my mind. A devil such as Raphael can't truly be trusted.
Agreed. There's not much we can do but press forward.
Grand Duke-to-be, eh, Wyll? I hope you don't forget about us little people, after you've ascended.
Seems like Wyll's a Grand Duke-to-be. I hope he remembers us little people, after he's ascended.
And watch out for Raphael. He's better at getting into people's heads than you are, you ass.
What do you think?
Feels like we're nearly at the end, one way or the other...

EditorData.NodeContext: A little nervous. History soon in the making.

Text.Value: My point is that Raphael was stirring the pot - trying to unsettle us.
I don't want this for Karlach; I won't allow it.
... except you decide blindly.
Do that again and I'll leave you to bleed out in this wilderness, understand?
I'll miss Astarion... though perhaps my neck won't.
Jaheira must be tired - forced to prolong her duty, her life. No potential successor has met her standards, I suppose.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 157 - Jaheira Timeless Body Scroll kept

Text.Value: It seems your fellow githyanki are keen to reclaim the artefact I carry. I can't afford that to happen.
It seems the githyanki are keen to reclaim the artefact I carry. I can't afford that to happen.
Things won't be the same, without Astarion. At least he got to enjoy his moment of triumph... before we betrayed him.

EditorData.NodeContext: Conflicted/thoughtful. She and the player sided against Astarion, who is now dead.

Text.Value: Use your shared connection to read her thoughts.
You accepted Bhaal, after everything we've been through? I can only hope this is part of some clever scheme I'm not privy to. Otherwise you might as well have stayed with the Absolute.
Did you have any strange dreams of late...? Vivid ones?

EditorData.NodeContext: Questioning/disquietened. Just had a very vivd dream

Text.Value: Perhaps we truly have a secret protector - or we're walking into a trap.
Those Gur Hunters made things difficult for themselves - they should really have tried to kill you before you became a vampire lord.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 151 - Defeated the Gur Hunters with Vampire Lord Astarion (Avatar only)

Text.Value: Sacrifice Orpheus, sacrifice the githyanki people to an eternity of Vlaakith's tyranny. I will not allow it.
We shouldn't have allowed the likes of Aradin to get the drop on us. Better be careful in future.

EditorData.NodeContext: Referring to an ambush they repelled from their camp

Text.Value: I'm still unsure. He could be a help to us, or not.
It seems like Cazador used Astarion's flesh not as a canvas, but as a contract. We haven't heard the last of this, I'll wager.
You're twisting my words - trying to manipulate me.
Baldur's Gate... you know, I never quite believed I'd actually make it back. Wasn't until we got within reach of Wyrm's Crossing that it felt real.
Blessings from afar...? Perhaps Mystra is more invested in you than it seems, Gale.
I had another dream - which I suppose means you did as well.
I understand your determination. But we still need a decision.
Good. You got there eventually.
Perhaps you're right. Perhaps a devil has our best interests at heart and wants nothing in return.
If you think that's for the best... but I just hope the Emperor doesn't betray our trust.
You'd think I'd have more sympathy for someone trapped in a pod, but perhaps we should have left Mizora where we found her.
So Cazador saw fit to carve his ambitions right into your flesh, Astarion. If I was you, I'd return the favour with interest.
That face-thief Orin's made off with Gale. We'll need to rescue him... unless we actually intend to kill Gortash for her.
There are many. But they all renounce their gods when they are taught fear.
Good. That's what I wanted to hear.
But let us not forget that we also have the Orphic Hammer. We could free Orpheus, let him wield the stones - if we can trust him.
I've made you doubt yourself. Sorry, not what I intended.
It was bad enough having just one of those tadpoles forced upon us. I can scarcely believe you actually inflicted another on yourself...
It seems you have made up with Mystra, Gale. Congratulations - though I don't see any such reconciliation between myself and Shar any time soon...
It seems you have made up with Mystra, Gale. Congratulations. Lady Shar has no love for your goddess... but I am glad you have someone to turn to.

EditorData.NodeContext: Supportive 'Reconciliation' = SH turned from Shar. 'No love for your goddess' = SH is loyal to Shar
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 177 - Avatar Gale met Mystra - forgiven

Text.Value: ... isn't it terrible when someone causes you to doubt yourself?
The Gauntlet of Shar is no ordinary temple - it is the highest test of the Dark Lady's faithful, to judge if they are worthy of becoming a Dark Justiciar.
Now, as for this 'Raphael'...
I suppose Astarion is a part of the vampire aristocracy now. I hope he doesn't expect us to bow to him.
Orin's little display was just intended to rattle us. We mustn't let her succeed... but need to stay alert, all the same.
We can't rely on the Harpers - not when Orin has them infested with shapeshifters. We're on our own - though I suppose we're used to it by now.
Wyrm's Crossing. We could be inside the city walls before long... and I could be back where this all started.
Be careful, consuming shadow magic. The darkness tends to take more than it gives. I would know.
You couldn't resist the allure of the shadows, Gale? I don't blame you - it's the only power that truly counts.
Orin's made off with Yenna. Either we mount a rescue... or we win her freedom with Gortash's life.
I think we've overstayed our welcome in this place - if we ever truly had one to begin with. We should leave.
Enough about me. What do you think is best?
If you can't control yourself, you're nothing but a liability.
Those vampire spawn came for you, didn't they Astarion? Good thing you're charming enough to fight for.
Those vampire spawn came for Astarion, didn't they? Lucky for him that we were here to fight them off...
The House of Hope - Raphael's abode. Only this time, he hasn't invited us to his table...
Karlach has offered to take on the duty. She doesn't have much time left, so there's a certain logic in leaving this to her. A somewhat callous logic, mind you.
Karlach has offered to take on the duty. She doesn't have much time left, so there's a certain logic in leaving this to her. The Dark Lady would approve, I'm sure.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'callous logic' = SH has turned from Shar. 'The dark lady would approve' = SH is loyal to Shar

Text.Value: Don't play coy. It happened to you as well, didn't it? It's all over your face.
Use your shared connection. Find out what she's thinking.

He slew Lady Shar's children - by rights I should avenge them and cut that ugly head right off his thick neck... but I'm no fool either. Picking a fight with him would be a distraction - a potentially fatal one.
Tell me what you know of the place.
So, one dead devil, and you might learn something new about yourself, Astarion. Seems promising... if you trust Raphael, that is.
It seems Viconia sought a greater purpose than Lady Shar had decided for her.
Shar did not come to Viconia's defence. All who bow to her are disposable pawns, in the end.
Overawed, of course... but I have scarce time to saviour the majesty of Lady Shar's domain - there is yet work to be done, in her name.
I see... then I hope she understands. But I trust your judgement.
A goddess abandoning you needn't be the end, Gale. Trust me, I know.
I'm sorry, Gale. To be abandoned by your goddess... I cannot imagine how that must feel. May the Dark Lady comfort you.
Poor Gale. I hope he knows that a goddess abandoning him needn't be the end - I know from experience.
Poor Gale. To be abandoned by his goddess... I cannot imagine how that must feel. May the Dark Lady comfort him.
This place is quite a find. Imagine all the people going about their lives, unaware of what their city has hidden away.
I suppose not many can boast that they've been to a githyanki crèche and survived. Perhaps that's a good omen for our chances going forward, if you're feeling optimistic.
All right. Perhaps we shouldn't trust Raphael. He is a devil, after all.
So, Jaheira is willing to embrace mortality - the ultimate form of retirement - and that's thanks to impressing her through your actions. Quite the compliment.
That crèche would be a smoking ruin if it wasn't for us. Still, better move along - I don't want to test the limits of your peoples' gratitude.
That crèche would be a smoking ruin if it wasn't for us. Still, better move along - I don't want to test the limits of githyanki gratitude.
So, the Stone Lord is Minsc, Jaheira's old acquaintance? Painfully small world, at times.
I've changed my mind. We shouldn't trust Raphael.
It feels like my entire world has been upended.
This... dream companion wanted me to use the tadpole - use its power. Whoever it was claimed to be an ally but... I don't know.
You had best hope Vlaakith appreciates your loyalty, Lae'zel. Otherwise I think you just killed a potential ally.
Lae'zel had better hope Vlaakith appreciates her loyalty. Otherwise, she achieved nothing but kill a potential ally.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 139 - Voss Camp/Lae'zel loyal to Vlaakith

Text.Value: So you've been walking around this whole time with some sort of magic bomb in your chest? I'm not normally one to begrudge someone their secrets, but that's something I should know...
So Gale's been walking around this whole time with some sort of magic bomb in his chest? I'm not normally one to begrudge someone their secrets, but that's something I should know...
We should be safe for the night now. Let's try and get some rest.

EditorData.NodeContext: Referring to an ambush they repelled from their camp

Text.Value: I can't believe Mystra actually expects Gale to just sacrifice himself like that. Seems like a waste of a fine mind.
We've made it to the Shadowfell - the very heart of the Gauntlet. How do you feel?
This is the place where you could become a Dark Justiciar. Your dream might soon be realised.
I know people who work much like our new acquaintance does.
Perhaps we shouldn't take Gortash's word for granted... but if he speaks the truth, we need to be careful. Orin could have eyes and ears on us right now.
I didn't expect you to turn on the Lich Queen so readily, Lae'zel. Wonders never cease.
I didn't expect Lae'zel to turn on the Lich Queen so readily. Wonders never cease.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 140 - Voss Camp/Lae'zel agreed to meet him

Text.Value: The Gauntlet has double meaning - it speaks of the ordeals to be overcome, and of the armour-clad fist of Lady Shar that would embrace the worthy. Survive the crushing gauntlet, and be embraced by the Nightsinger at its very core.
We've had a mind flayer whispering to us in our dreams all this time...? I really shouldn't be surprised by anything at this stage.
So you remain loyal to your queen? You're consistent, I'll give you that...
So Lae'zel remains loyal to her queen? She's consistent, I'll give her that...

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 142 - Vlaakith camp/Lae'zel Vlaakith path after

Text.Value: Karlach and Wyll seem to have put their differences aside. I thought it was going to come to blows for a moment.
This place seems remarkably tense for a sacred grove. Perhaps we shouldn't linger.
It was no easy thing, overcoming those urges that gripped you. I'm not sure I would have managed, in your shoes. Well done.
I respect his craft. As should you.
I'll tell you in due course. I just wanted to see how close we are in thinking, first of all.
Hmm. Or is it? Suddenly I'm not so sure...
I don't know what's worse. A devil or a prying leader.
You don't need a scourge or a rack to break people. Fear and self-doubt are sufficient.
There's nothing like a stroll through some sewers to keep your sense of self-importance in check.
Your father won't be around forever, Wyll. But the pact? That's a different matter. I hope you won't live to regret being sentimental.
It can't have been easy, to resign yourself to keeping the pact. But I'm glad you choose your father.
Wyll's father won't be around forever, but the pact? That's a different matter. I hope he won't live to regret being sentimental.
It can't have been easy, for Wyll to resign himself to the pact. But I'm glad he chose his father.
If this place is as inviting as other aspects of githyanki culture, we'll be in for an interesting time, to say the least...
Actually, if Raphael can truly offer help, maybe we should consider it.
He's clever. My order uses the same tactic when dealing with enemies of Shar.
It need not, indeed. I think you understand how important this is to me. I must prevail.
We need to keep pressing forward. The day isn't won until Ketheric Thorm has breathed his last.

EditorData.NodeContext: Some urgency. In the midst of a battle (though not in immediate danger)

Text.Value: What will you do to the Nightsong?
I'm glad I made the right decision then.
*She is testing you. About Raphael.*
Cunning people. Private. And very dangerous, at times. Perhaps you'll meet them one day...
So that's how you win Mystra's forgiveness - self-sacrifice? I'm sorry, Gale. That can't be what you wanted to hear.
I thought this camp was supposed to be our safe haven - not quite so when we wake up to dead tiefling bards. I may have difficulty sleeping for a while...
I think I've had my fill of underwater misadventures. Let's get back to the surface world before any more perils seek us out.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 113 - Return from the Iron Throne

Text.Value: The Netherbrain's lair must be close. This could all be over very soon, one way or another...
When actual pain comes, the victim's already done the heavy lifting for their torturer.
Use your shared connection. Listen to her thoughts.
So, only a mind flayer can wield the stones, from what the Emperor said. And not a part-illithid either - the full-blown thing.
So, only a mind flayer can wield the stones, from what the Emperor said.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 173 - Learned that for the Netherstone to be effective, the avatar needs to be a mind flayer

Text.Value: I may have to rely on your local knowledge, to plug the gaps in my own mind. Hopefully I'll remember more than I expect to.
I spoke to Karlach already - I agreed to let her transform. This is what she wants.
Seems like you have a particular point you want to make about Raphael.
The artefact is shielding us, but ultimately, you wish to give it away? Something has to give.
So, the githyanki have no cure for our condition - unless you count death as a cure. I won't pretend to be surprised.
Normally it would not be for me to pursue becoming a Dark Justiciar without a superior's command, but this is different. My lady wanted me to find this place, I know it.
Oh you were tempted, were you? Interesting.
The mission she sent me on was a lie - same as everything else she ever told me.
*Anticipation. She is testing you somehow. About Raphael.*
Whoever's reaching out to us truly does seem opposed to the Absolute - but wants us to embrace the tadpole? Venture right into the heart of the cult?
Sounds like a good idea.
So, you're free from your hunger, free from any lingering fear of the sun... but all those lives you sacrificed, Astarion. I'm not sure I'll forget their final screams any time soon.
'Vampire Ascendant'. A fine prize, Astarion, paid for with a sea of blood. I'm glad to know I have an ally who understands the value of sacrifice - congratulations.
Gale defied Mystra herself. Good - not every goddess is deserving of such love. I would know.
Gale defied Mystra herself. I hope he does not come to regret it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Reflective. 'I would knoiw' = SH turned from Shar. 'I hope he does  not come to regret it' = SH loyal to Shar.
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 182 - COM Gale met Mystra - defied

Text.Value: I don't know how exactly Orin managed to spirit away someone as big as Halsin, but we have to get him back - either via a rescue, or Gortash's death.
So, you've committed to being the Blade of Frontiers. None can doubt you've earned the title. Well done.
It seems that Wyll's determined to remain the Blade of Frontiers. I suppose he's truly earned the moniker, now.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 134 - Wyll Blade of Frontiers Decision

Text.Value: Karlach... you must have a lot to think about, just now. If you need time to yourself, take it.
Poor Karlach. All this way, just to be faced with a dead end - literally. I can't imagine how she feels.
What happened to that magical item, Gale...?
Gale, you truly thought to turn to shadow magic, after seeing how it has ravaged nature? Your ambitions are... disquieting.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 175 - Gale has crafted the Dark Lantern

Text.Value: This place makes my skin crawl. Don't take anything for granted in here.
He's a pompous sack of spare parts. He and his undead lackeys should never have come here. Perhaps I can rid Lady Shar's gauntlet of them yet...
This is it. Win or lose, the fate of the city - of everything - is going to be decided here.
Back on your feet? Good - we do have some matters to take care of, you know.
Gale's back on his feet - good. We've got enough problems as it is without him dead as well.
Your opinions are easily swayed. Should I wait for them to change again?
No matter. I hope I never have to think of her again.
And aren't you glad that I am?
Minsc - he seemed to believe that doppelganger was truly Jaheira. A sure sign he's being manipulated.
I know you have your personal demons to contend with... but if I didn't make it clear before, I think you can beat this. Just don't give in, and seek help if you need it.
A cruel end. I wouldn't have wished that for Zevlor, no matter his failings.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sombre. Zevlor's mutilated corpse was discovered

Text.Value: We're in decidedly unfamiliar territory now - keep up the pressure, and stay alert. We need to find Thorm.
If you say so. But we still need a decision.
We have the hammer - now is the time to use it. We'll release Orpheus.
Astarion. You seem remarkably hale and hearty, in spite of all we're facing. The itinerant lifestyle must suit you.
It will be me. I'll become illithid. I'm not afraid.
An imposter in our ranks... if this is true, it could be anyone. You, me... well, not me - I know who I am.
If Raphael can truly offer help, we have to at least consider it.
That temper of yours is a sight to behold. You'll need to be careful, or your rage will burn right through you.
Karlach's temper is a sight to behold. She'll need to be careful, or that rage will burn her right out.
I suppose I am. Though the chance to savour the moment might be brief, given all that still lies ahead of us.
Lady Shar's power will soon fade from these lands, but it is a price that had to be paid, so that the traitor Ketheric Thorm could face justice at last.
The shadows are losing their grip on these lands - Shar can indeed be thwarted. Comforting to know.
It's good to be back.
We need to make a decision - if anyone's to become a mind flayer, perhaps it should be Karlach. She's doomed either way.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 132 - Orpheus Decision - wants Karlach mind flayer

Text.Value: There were no right answers with that devil. He was toying with his food - us.
What grabbed you, exactly? His parlour tricks? His manners? The lavish spread, even?
This isn't over yet - we need to pursue Ketheric Thorm.
So, only a mind flayer can wield the stones, from what the Emperor said. And not a part-illithid either - the full-blown thing.
So, only a mind flayer can wield the stones, from what the Emperor said.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 174 - Learned that for the Netherstone to be effective, the avatar or companion Karlach needs to be a mind flayer

Text.Value: Perhaps you didn't.
We do have the Orphic Hammer. We could unleash Orpheus, let him wield the stones - provided we're willing to trust him.
It happened to you as well?
She should have just obeyed - forgotten about the artefact. Then perhaps she could have still served the Nightsinger... under me, of course.
That's Orin dealt with - good riddance. Now that we have her Netherstone, we're one big step closer to finishing this, once and for all.
Whatever you choose to do, you can count on my support.
Just our luck to find an inn, only for it to be burning to the ground.
You sacrificed your own father, Wyll? Not a step that many could take, but the Nightsinger would appreciate your resolve, I think.
You... you sacrificed your own father? I hope freedom from the pact was worth it.
Wyll sacrificed his own father to be free of the pact. Remarkable resolve, if you can harden your heart. The Nightsinger would approve.
Wyll sacrificed his own father... I hope freedom from the pact is worth it to him.
My mind is settled. Raphael could be just the friend we need.
Leave.
Not the worst prospect we've stumbled across. As long as you can look past what he is...
An infestation of vampire spawn - that's just about the last thing I wanted to wake up to. We thwarted their efforts to seize Astarion, at least.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 143 - Vampire spawn attack/Astarion taken away

Text.Value: This place seems ancient. It must predate everything on the surface. I wonder what it was like in its heyday.
We can't just let Orin take one of our own - even if it's Lae'zel. We have to rescue her... or kill Gortash in order to win her freedom.
Very well...
I'll never be able to look at a butcher shop again after this place. But at least we were afforded a soft landing.
Defying a goddess, Gale? Well, they do say imitation is a form of flattery. I just hope you know what you're doing.
Defying a goddess, Gale? Bold, but Mystra was never worthy of your love.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little surprised. 'imitation is a form of flattery' = SH turned from Shar. 'Never worthy of  your love' = SH loyal to Shar
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 179 - Avatar Gale met Mystra - defied

Text.Value: What's your point exactly? Spit it out.
Use your shared connection to hear her thoughts.
I can't believe Mystra actually expects Gale to just sacrifice himself like that. Seems like a waste of a fine mind.
Whatever Lady Shar bids me to. I must not fail her now - not when I'm so close...
So Cazador wishes to ascend at your expense? Somehow, I doubt you intend to accept that meekly.
So Cazador wishes to ascend at Astarion's expense? Somehow I can't see our fanged friend accepting that meekly.
The old ways were lost over time - now some claim the rank simply by killing a single Selûnite. But before, they were a true elite. Many would attempt the trials, but few would succeed.
I never thought I'd see the Gauntlet of Shar for myself. In fact, part of me wondered if it was actually real.
The Orphic Hammer is ours - which means we could free Orpheus, if we wish.
I'm sorry that happened to you, Wyll - that bat-winged slattern deserves to meet the business end of a poo-scraper.

EditorData.NodeContext: Poo-scraper is an in-game dagger. Anger/empathy for Wyll
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 187 - Wyll is a devil (Wyll Avatar)

Text.Value: I'll admit it - I don't know what to do.
The Underdark... as if we didn't face enough dangers back up on the surface.
But I can hardly hold that against you - you seemed as surprised as I was. If you're able to resist your urges, then surely you can resist the lure of past allegiances also.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quietly taken aback/unpacking what she's learned (dark urge player had in the past been a leader of the Absolute cult, but no longer remembers)

Text.Value: I think I detected a note of admiration in your voice.
None of us are about to turn into an illithid. I shall give the stones to the Emperor.
We can't hedge our bets here. Best we decide how to deal with him, if at all.
I can't believe Mystra actually expects Gale to just sacrifice himself like that. Seems like a waste of a fine mind.
So, a deal's been struck with Raphael at least. He certainly drew out his sales pitch for long enough.
Help is help, no matter the source.
I hope Mizora flies into the blades of a windmill for what she did to Wyll... though I must admit the new look is a little dashing...

EditorData.NodeContext: Anger/empaty for Wyll, though she also likes the horns.
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 187 - Wyll is a devil (Wyll companion)

Text.Value: So Astarion didn't fulfil his master's ambitions for himself. At least that means he's his own man... though I'm a little surprised he didn't covet those powers.
I suppose it is. Though the chance to savour the moment might be brief, given all that still lies ahead of us.
I only know what I know... I was ordered to retrieve it, and that's what I intend to do. The rest is immaterial to me.
Very well. Let's do all we can to help her.
You're obviously toying with me. Stop it.
These trials - need it even be said that you want to undertake them.
I don't know what you're talking about.
Minthara with child... Somehow I can't picture her sitting around the campfire, knitting baby booties...

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 152 - Minthara told her romance partner that she's pregnant

Text.Value: Boo seems like a worthy addition to our group. His pet, Minsc, may prove useful also.
Shar's power still grips this land. A shame we could not banish it - it would have felt good to spite her.
This land remains cloaked by Lady Shar's power - good. A shame it cost us Halsin as a travelling companion though. He may have been misguided, but I liked looking at him.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 168 - Shadow Curse not lifted/Halsin Gone

Text.Value: Ironic. She tried to cling to Lady Shar's good graces, but that just hastened her downfall.
But if it's any consolation, the new look is rather rugged...
Actually... yes, you're right. Very intuitive. Clearly the devil was trying to sow doubt among us.
See? Sowing doubt is an old trick. Watch out for it. And for Raphael.
That's the last of Raphael. I'll be glad to no longer have to suffer his smug face.
Not the cheeriest of inns, this place. But I suppose the mortal peril lurking just past the firelight is liable to put a dampener on the mood.
I'm not going to just change my mind. We can't trust Raphael.
Minsc is dead, Jaheria is gone... We've lost ourselves some powerful allies, I fear. Let's just hope we still have enough strength to see this through.
Karlach... that was a decidedly mixed blessing you received. My sympathies... but at least you can seek comfort now.
Poor Karlach. She can finally seek out the touch of another... only to be told she might not have much time left.
But let's at least see if there's a healer to be found, first of all.
She sowed her own downfall in trying to take the prism for herself. Had she never sent me, I'd still bow to Shar, none the wiser...
The crèche... it's nothing but rubble and ashes now. We should put some distance between ourselves and this mess, before any githyanki come investigating.
That drow, Nere, is going to be on his last gasp unless someone digs him out. Though not necessarily our concern, of course.
You know, failing to make a decision is the same as making a decision...
It seems like Wyll and Karlach will play nice from now on. Saves us having to pick sides.
Who the hells are these people you know, who do such things?
In fact, none of us can. That thing is shielding us, somehow. I don't want to know what happens if we lose it.
It's so strange - I don't remember much of it, yet I can't help feel like I know it. It feels like home.
We need to make a decision - and you becoming a mind flayer seems like the least-worst option, unfortunately.

EditorData.NodeContext: Some outrage. A great sacrifice is being asked of the party.

Text.Value: I suppose it was a lot to take in. A devil sought us out, teased us with his help...
Most would think us mad for wandering right into the middle of a goblin war clan... I suppose that goes to demonstrate just how desperate we are.
Let's not find out. We have enough to contend with already.
Watch out for that devil.
So Gale just consumes magical items like I do wine? We truly are a group apart...
I must admit, I'm feeling less sure all of a sudden.
No matter. Her loss is my gain. Lady Shar wills it.
I consumed it - I had no choice.
That orthon lurking in the wings is formidable - we should be careful around him.
Gortash is no more - and he was kind enough to bequeath his Netherstone to us. We might yet manage to pull this off.
Astarion's an interesting find. Let's hope any future acquaintances don't hold a blade to your throat by way of introduction.
So Lorroakan covets Dame Aylin? He'll live to regret that, once we inform her.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 155 - Lorroakan states his intention to retrieve Nightsong

Text.Value: It seems like we can't escape this mess, in the waking world or otherwise.
I've changed my mind. Perhaps we should trust Raphael.
I can't believe Mystra actually expects Gale to just sacrifice himself like that. Seems like a waste of a fine mind.
This place reeks of madness and murder - I can almost feel it in the rotten air.
We could throw ourselves at his feet - be they cloven or otherwise. Or perhaps we shouldn't.
I just hope he's able to keep his hunger in check.
You must have found something alluring, to overlook the fact he was a devil.
Very well. Whatever happens, I shall stand by you.
Let's take time to think about it. Some food and rest, things will be clear then.
I've heard you can't get blood from a stone, but apparently you can get a wizard from one. Gale seems interesting.
Bloody hells - literally. Just when I think I've got a grasp on our dilemma, a devil shows up...

EditorData.NodeContext: 'WTF...?' - the universe keeps throwing her curveballs, and this latest one is a doozy

Text.Value: Sacrifice Orpheus, sacrifice the githyanki people to an eternity of Vlaakith's tyranny. I will not allow it.
You clearly can't be trusted.
I expect we'll be parting company very soon.
I thought perhaps you'd be tempted to seize Cazador's prize in his stead... but you didn't. Perhaps that makes you the better man - I'm sure all those people you spared would agree.
I thought perhaps you'd be tempted to seize Cazador's prize in his stead... but you didn't. Pity - a vampire lord would have been a fine ally... but no matter. It's done.
Maybe...
If... if you're sure. This is not a decision to make in haste, but you have my support, either way.
He's a devil. We shouldn't trust him - simple as that.
I know. I can scarcely believe it's real, but I saw it with my own eyes, felt the polished stone walls raised in Lady Shar's honour...
Honestly? I'm not so sure.
Clearly. And do you know what? I think that's just what that devil intended.
Mizora is no more... but we sacrificed Wyll along with her. The Hells have him now.
No. My mind is made up.
Still... it seems keen to be an ally, in its own way. Compared to what we're up against, I'm not sure that's a bad thing.
It seems even the Lord of Murder has lost faith in you. I'd offer my commiserations, but, well... I think they might be lost on you.
Not for me to shed tears over a Selûnite like Isobel, but you condemned a lot of people when you struck her down. People we could have had use of.
A lot of people died because you lost the run of yourself. Isobel shielded them from the shadows - and you left them vulnerable.
A problem for another time. Hopefully we'll no longer be in need of protection by the time my mission draws to an end.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'we'll cross that bridge when we come to it'

Text.Value: A vampire nest - you truly can find everything in the city. I'd better keep my throat protected...
I hope that amulet proves to be worth it...
Glad to be back, I take it?
Why the hells did she want the prism? It cost her everything.
The decision is made - no point in regrets now. Let's keep going.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 112 - Orpheus Brain consumption / Turning into a mindflayer

Text.Value: That Orphic Hammer could be crucial... we may have to try and get our hands on it.
What did you think of it?
Whatever Mizora has in store for you, I doubt it's anything good.
Wyll ought to know what happened with Mizora. Whatever she has in store for him can't be good.
Karlach. Facing your own mortality in such a... definitive manner must be hard. I'm sorry. If it's any consolation, the rest of us are still liable to perish anyway.
Poor Karlach, having to face her own mortality in such a... definitive manner. Though the rest of us are still liable to perish, if it's any consolation.

EditorData.NodeContext: Empathy/hint of gallows humour at the end.

Text.Value: What delightful circumstances we find ourselves in.
So who are Shar's enemies? Who receives this treatment?
He knows our secret, he claims he can help... what do you make of him?
That... creature you turned into. I hope you have it under control. It didn't look like something I'd want to contend with.

EditorData.NodeContext: Apprehensive. Player transformed into a large monster previously

Synopsis:
Shadowheart topical greeting dialog. Contains all of her topical greetings.
